## Candidate Profiles
**Base URL**: `/candidate-profiles`

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Payload (Body) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `POST` | `/candidate-profiles` | Create a profile | `CandidateProfileCreateRequest` (JSON) |
| `GET` | `/candidate-profiles/list` | List all profiles | - |
| `GET` | `/candidate-profiles/{id}` | Get profile by ID | - |
| `POST` | `/candidate-profiles/update/{id}` | Update profile | `CandidateProfileUpdateRequest` (JSON) |
| `DELETE` | `/candidate-profiles/{id}` | Delete profile | - |

---
**Note**: Most `POST` requests require `Content-Type: application/json`, except for `/users/UpdateUser/{id}` which uses `@ModelAttribute` and likely expects `multipart/form-data` or `x-www-form-urlencoded`.
